defaultThe proposals are vague as to how the res
defaultidence test will be satisfied. Our members 
defaultsupport marginalised groups like domestic violence victims and child migrants and have drawn attention to the difficulties that clients will face when they need to provide evidence about residence and legal status. The residence test
default will present a bar to 
defaultthose who will be eligible for legal aid but unable to prove it.
default&#xa0;
defaultWorse still, the proposals will ine
defaultvitably result in those in despe
defaultrate need of legal help be
defaulting prevented from getting it. 
defaultThis will not only have dire consequences for the people involved but will promote a culture of impunity where abuse and unlawful action against those who cannot afford to pay for legal aid will go unchecked.  This is unacceptable in our view and will weak
defaulten the 
defaultrule of law by creating a two-t
defaulti
defaulte
defaultr justice system.
